Q: Angular Unit Test Error: 1 component threw errors during cleanup at TestBedRender3.destroyActiveFixtures A: <p>Ensure that the declaration of your subscription variable is intialised. For instance:</p>
<p>This will fail:</p>
<pre><code>subscription: Subscription;

ngOnInit() {
  this.subscription.add(...);
}

ngOnDestroy() {
  this.subscription.unsubscribe();
}
</code></pre>
<p>This should work:</p>
<pre><code>subscription: Subscription = new Subscription(); // see initialization

ngOnInit() {
  this.subscription.add(...);
}

ngOnDestroy() {
  this.subscription.unsubscribe();
}
</code></pre>

Q: How can I create the Netflix Hero Curved Divider with CSS Radial Gradient? A: <p>here is an idea:</p>
<p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false" data-console="true" data-babel="false" data-babel-preset-react="false" data-babel-preset-ts="false">
<div class="snippet-code">
<pre class="snippet-code-css lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>.box {
  height: 100px;
  background: linear-gradient(90deg,#0000, red 20% 80%,#0000); /* the coloration */
  clip-path: ellipse(60% 100% at bottom); /* don't touch the 100%, adjust only the 60% to control the curve */
  mask: radial-gradient(62% 95% at bottom,#0000 98%,#000); 
  /* 62% = 60% of the clip-path + little something you can adjust 
     95% = 100% of the clip-path - little something you can adjust
  */
}


body {
  height: 100vh;
  margin: 0;
  display: grid;
  align-items: end;
  background: #000;
}</code></pre>
<pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;div class="box"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
</p>
